🔧 Final Specification for cvehunter
You’re building a CLI-based Go tool that:

Searches public GitHub repositories for CVE exploits and by default list the latest 20 cves  with name and description only

Extracts metadata like CVE ID, description, tags (e.g., RCE, XSS), severity, date, language

Supports multiple filters (tag, language, severity, date)

Can save results to file

Optional: GitHub token support, live preview, offline cache, etc.


Features You Asked For (Reconfirmed)
Feature	Status	Notes
--cve lookup	✅	Done
--tags filtering	✅ (not -tag)	You typed -tag — actual is --tags
--lang filtering	✅	Done
--severity filter	✅	Done
--after / --before date filter	⚠️ Not implemented yet	You used --after, not added yet
--outfile to save results	✅	Done
--max results per CVE	✅	Done
--sort (stars / updated)	✅	Done
--verbose	✅	Done
